Mobile Legends: Bang Bang (MLBB) is a popular mobile multiplayer online battle arena (MOBA) game developed and published by Moonton. Players control a character, known as a "hero," and participate in 5v5 battles with the objective of destroying the enemy's base while defending their own. The game features various modes, including ranked matches, classic matches, and a variety of arcade modes.

MLBB has a significant esports presence, with numerous tournaments held worldwide, including the Mobile Legends Southeast Asia Cup (MSC), the Mobile Legends Professional League (MPL), and the annual M1 World Championship. These tournaments attract top teams and players, showcasing high-level gameplay and strategies.
